						<p><hi rend="italic">Pedestal of a Jaina Tīrthaṅkara image.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th-13th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th-13th Century A.D.,</hi> states that the image of Pārśva-Bhaṭṭāraka was presented to the Kusuva-jīnālaya of Yāpanīyasaṁgha and Vṛksha-mūla[gaṇa], by Kāḷiseṭṭi of <hi rend="bold">Oṛeyūr (?).</hi></p>						

